<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

Turn any tiddler into a //dashboard//: a free-form canvas onto which you drop other tiddlers as freely arrangeable tiles. Each tile transcludes a target tiddler; you move it, resize it, restyle it, and click it to open the underlying tiddler in the story river.

Tag a tiddler with <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">> and a view-template body cascade entry swaps its body for the dashboard canvas — no special editor, no separate app.

!! Key features

* ''Drop to add'' — drag any tiddler from the wiki onto the canvas and it becomes a tile. Or type a title and press //Add tile//.
* ''Free-form layout'' — absolute pixel positioning; drag a tile to move, drag its bottom-right corner to resize. Geometry is saved on release.
* ''Bring-to-front z-order'' — interacting with a tile raises it above the others; the stacking order persists.
* ''Two tile styles'' — a //window// tile with a title bar and controls, or a //bare// tile that is just the resizable content.
* ''Click to open'' — a click (as opposed to a drag) opens the tile's target tiddler in the story river.
* ''Plain-field storage'' — every tile is its own system tiddler with ordinary editable fields (`x`, `y`, `w`, `h`, `z`, `target`, `style`). No JSON blobs.

!! Quick start

# Click ''New dashboard'' in the page controls (right sidebar → Tools), or tag any tiddler <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">>.
# Drag a few tiddlers onto the canvas.
# Move, resize, and restyle them; click one to open it.

See the ''Examples'' tab for concrete recipes and ''Reference'' for the full field and tag list.

